name: GoogleTasks
title: GoogleTasks
description: Google Tasks is a free online service that helps manage your to-do lists.

endpoints.name: updateTaskList
endpoints.description: Updates the authenticated user's specified task list.

endpoints.name: updateTask
endpoints.description: Creates a new task on the specified task list.

endpoints.name: revokeAccessToken
endpoints.description: In some cases a user may wish to revoke access given to an application. A user can revoke access by visiting Account Settings. It is also possible for an application to programmatically revoke the access given to it. Programmatic revocation is important in instances where a user unsubscribes or removes an application. In other words, part of the removal process can include an API request to ensure the permissions granted to the application are removed.
